claims:
1. A method of classifying a breast cancer intrinsic subtype in a test sample comprising:
a) obtaining a gene expression profile for each of a plurality of training breast cancer samples that have been classified according to breast cancer intrinsic subtype, wherein each of the Luminal A (LumA), Luminal B (LumB), Basal-like (Basal), HER2-enriched (HER2), and Normal-like (Normal) intrinsic subtypes is represented in the plurality of breast cancer samples, and wherein the gene expression profile is based on expression of substantially all of the intrinsic genes listed in Table 1;
b) using a supervised algorithm to construct centroids for each of the breast cancer intrinsic subtypes in the training set;
c) obtaining a gene expression profile for said test sample, wherein the gene expression profile is based on expression of the intrinsic genes listed in Table 1;
d) comparing the gene expression profile of the test sample to the centroids constructed in step (b);
e) calculating the distance of the gene expression profile of the test sample to each of the centroids; and,
f) assigning the test sample to one of the breast cancer intrinsic subtypes based upon the nearest centroid.

5. A method of predicting outcome in a test subject having breast cancer comprising:
a) obtaining a gene expression profile for each of a plurality of training breast cancer samples that have been classified according to breast cancer intrinsic subtype, wherein each of the Luminal A (LumA), Luminal B (LumB), Basal-like (Basal), HER2-enriched (HER2), and Normal-like (Normal) intrinsic subtypes is represented in the plurality of breast cancer samples, wherein outcome in said samples is known, and wherein the gene expression profile is based on expression of substantially all of the intrinsic genes listed in Table 1;
b) using a supervised algorithm to construct centroids for each of the breast cancer intrinsic subtypes in the training set;
c) calculating a risk score for each training breast cancer sample by fitting a regression model to the gene expression profiles obtained in step (a), wherein the regression model accounts for the similarity of each gene expression profile to the centroids constructed in step (b);
d) stratifying the risk scores obtained in step (c) into higher and lower risk groups;
e) obtaining a gene expression profile from a breast cancer sample from said test subject, wherein the gene expression profile is based on expression of substantially all of the intrinsic genes listed in Table 1;
f) comparing the gene expression profile of the test sample to the centroids constructed in step (b);
g) calculating the distance of the gene expression profile of the test sample to each of the centroids;
h) calculating a risk score using the regression model of step (c) and the distance to each centroid obtained in step (f); and
i) determining whether said test subject falls within a higher or a lower risk group by comparing the risk score obtained in step (h) to the risk groups assigned in step (d), wherein assignment to a lower risk group indicates a more favorable outcome, and assignment to a higher risk group indicate a less favorable outcome.
